        "content": "<p>Currently, the only way i know to deal with implications is by using <code>intro</code> in tactic mode and <code>fun</code> for constructing terms. Both are a bit weird for the following:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Doing <code>intro</code> here just gives a redundant hypothesis and doing <code>fun h=&gt; hq</code> is weird for the same reason. Is there an implication constructor that takes <code>hp</code> <code>hq</code> and gives an object of type <code>p \\implies q</code></p>",
        "id": 449360458,
        "sender_full_name": "Jad Abou Hawili",
        "timestamp": 1720199870
    },
